ation: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000=
000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">tontine</a>=E2=80=
=9D refers to the fact that some of the warrants issued to the SPAC=E2=80=
=99s investors have this sort of the-people-who-stay-divide-up-the-warrants=
-of-the-people-who-quit property.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And now G=
ary Cohn=E2=80=99s SPAC is doing it, sort of. Last Friday, Cohn Robbins Hol=
dings Corp., a SPAC, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cli=
ck/26493398.266627/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE4=
